    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="189"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d189">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 704.9318/5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 40.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 21, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 15th instant, in which you are good enough to inform me that
                    the Costa Rican Government has consented to the exercise of good offices by
                    American diplomatic and consular representatives in behalf of Chinese lawfully
                    resident in that country.</p>
                <pb facs="0296" n="180" xml:id="pg_180"/>
                <p>I beg to express to you the sincere thanks of my Government for this act of true
                    friendship shown by the American Government toward China, which, I need hardly
                    assure you, is gratefully appreciated by the Chinese residents in Costa Rica as
                    well as by myself.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kai Fu Shah</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
